Well, that is a very serious problem, and there I 
blame the United States educational system for

43:31.341 --> 43:43.498
not insisting that everybody learn at least one 
foreign language while he's growing up, because

43:31.341 --> 43:43.498
my experience has been if you learn one, you can 
learn two. But when you've learned a second

43:44.360 --> 43:48.686
language, you can learn a third language very 
easily. If you've never learned any language

43:49.567 --> 43:51.910
except your own, By the age of 40, it's almost 
impossible to learn a foreign language, and it is a

43:52.244 --> 43:56.228
problem. And Americans have much more 
difficulty, in general, now there are very

43:56.389 --> 44:08.923
specific examples to the contrary, but in 
general, have much more difficulty learning a

43:56.389 --> 44:08.923
foreign language than most overseas people or 
foreigners. And it is a problem in doing their jobs

44:10.084 --> 44:15.450
and in making themselves feel at home in a foreign 
country. How many South American countries,

44:17.523 --> 44:22.910
well, many of them have unstable governments. How 
does this affect the lifestyle of Americans

44:22.991 --> 44:26.535
overseas? Well, the degree of instability, 
again, is relative. In Brazil, for example, the

44:30.220 --> 44:34.106
government was very, very stable. The lifestyle 
was totally free, no problems. In 1972, 1973 in

44:37.851 --> 44:42.738
Argentina, the government was totally unstable. 
